* Subversion Configuration Files

   This is client configuration to ignore all generated files and directories.
Also for proper mime-type and eol-style for new files in SVN

   To install copy https://pyx4j.com/svn/trunk/src/env/subversion/subversion_config to "%APPDATA%\Subversion\config on Windows and ~/.subversion/config on Unix

   See the files in your local source tree: src\env\subversion


* Eclipse Java Code Style

    Code style is required to simplify patches contribution to the project.

    Configure naming conventions, style rules and comment settings in Eclipse. Upload templates from https://pyx4j.com/svn/trunk/src/env/eclipse

    See the files in your local source tree: src\env\eclipse

    * In Eclipse IDE Use Window > Preferences > Java > Code Style > Formatter  [Import]  select file 'code-formater.xml'

    * Java > Code Style > Clean Up  [Import]  use the file 'clean-up.xml' from the same location.

    * Java > Code Style > Code Templates [Import] use the file 'code-templates.xml'

    * Java > Code Style > Organize Imports  [Import]  use the file 'code.importorder'

    * Java > Editor > Save Actions select all sugested actions. This will format the code on each save.  See the screenshot

